{"symbol": "CALCOCO2", "uniprot": "Q13137", "protein_name": "Calcium-binding and coiled-coil domain-containing protein 2", "length": 446, "function": "Xenophagy-specific receptor required for autophagy-mediated intracellular bacteria degradation. Acts as an effector protein of galectin-sensed membrane damage that restricts the proliferation of infecting pathogens such as Salmonella typhimurium upon entry into the cytosol by targeting LGALS8-associated bacteria for autophagy (PubMed:22246324). Initially orchestrates bacteria targeting to autophagosomes and subsequently ensures pathogen degradation by regulating pathogen-containing autophagosome maturation (PubMed:23022382, PubMed:25771791). Bacteria targeting to autophagosomes relies on its interaction with MAP1LC3A, MAP1LC3B and/or GABARAPL2, whereas regulation of pathogen-containing autophagosome maturation requires the interaction with MAP3LC3C (PubMed:23022382, PubMed:25771791). May play a role in ruffle formation and actin cytoskeleton organization and seems to negatively regulate constitutive secretion (PubMed:17635994)", "ensembl_gene": "ENSG00000136436", "scores": {"selectivity": 0.1194, "protein_drug": 0.584, "rna_drug": 0.786}, "flags": {"surface": false, "enzyme": true, "mod_aso": true, "mod_sirna": false}, "details": {"nominated_modality": "ASO", "winning_axis": "RNA", "quadrant": "Both viable", "best_route": "small molecule", "sm_score": "0.739", "sirna_score": "0.443", "aso_score": "0.689"}, "modality": "ASO", "structure": "data/structures/CALCOCO2.pdb", "pockets": [{"rank": 1, "druggability": 0.213, "volume": 503.8, "residues": [44, 45, 46, 48, 50, 78, 80, 81, 83, 86, 87, 89]}, {"rank": 2, "druggability": 0.086, "volume": 322.4, "residues": [290, 293, 294, 297]}, {"rank": 3, "druggability": 0.078, "volume": 392.8, "residues": [137, 138, 141, 142, 144, 145, 148]}], "links": [{"key": "uniprot", "label": "UniProt", "url": "https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/Q13137"}, {"key": "alphafold", "label": "AlphaFol